There are two kinds of problems in your Java code:

---

In your Java code you have properties of type `List&lt;...&gt;`
  
    @JacksonXmlProperty(localName = &quot;duplication&quot;)
    List&lt;CodeClone&gt; codeClones;
  
  and

    @JacksonXmlProperty(localName = &quot;file&quot;)
	List&lt;SourceFiles&gt; files;
	  
You need do annotate these `List` properties
also with `@JacksonXmlWrapper(useWrapping = false)`.
If you omit this, then the default would be `useWrapping = true`
and Jackson would expect for example

    &lt;file&gt;  
      &lt;file&gt;...&lt;/file&gt;
	  &lt;file&gt;...&lt;/file&gt;
	&lt;/file&gt;
  
instead of just
  
    &lt;file&gt;...&lt;/file&gt;
	&lt;file&gt;...&lt;/file&gt;

See also the [Java doc of `@JacksonXmlElementWrapper`][1].

---

In your XML example you have several XML attributes
(like  `line=&quot;126&quot;`or `path=&quot;Some\Path\Here&quot;`)
which are of course different from
XML elements (like `&lt;line&gt;126&lt;/line&gt;` or
`&lt;path&gt;Some\Path\Here&lt;/path&gt;`).

You need to tell Jackson these are XML attributes by annotating
the Java property with `@JacksonXmlProperty(isAttribute = true)`.
If you omit this, then the default is `isAttribute = false`
and Jackson would expect an XML element instead of an XML attribute.

See also the [Java doc of `@JacksonXmlProperty`][2].

 [1]: http://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-dataformat-xml/javadoc/2.2.0/com/fasterxml/jackson/dataformat/xml/annotation/JacksonXmlElementWrapper.html
 [2]: http://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-dataformat-xml/javadoc/2.2.0/com/fasterxml/jackson/dataformat/xml/annotation/JacksonXmlProperty.html

